The paper focuses on information filtering on coupled social networks, which involves analyzing social and behavior information of online users. This topic is closely related to social networks (cs.SOC) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also proposes a hybrid algorithm, which involves data analysis and machine learning techniques, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the experimental results and empirical analyses presented in the paper involve statistical analysis and modeling, which falls under the category of social informatics (cs.SI).
